items.text: Soya milk: Whampoa Soya Bean #01-52 (in a corner) serves it freshly made. Children say it tastes even better (& more fragrant) than d famous Tiong Bahru stall! Lots of interesting items to sample
Lai Lai fried fish soup stall serves lots of veggie and fried fish taste good
Satay bee-hoon: 4get abt d other stalls (all w/o queues). Head straight 2 Liang Liang Cooked Food (shifted to #01-74). U get d real deal here.
robert's mee siam YUMM
Nanyang coffee is a must-try!
They will be having their renovation from the beg May till July.
Wanton noodle...Hoover rojak and of course. The one and 😉😉only fried prawn mee
Wahhhhhhhhhh, Hokkien Mee to die for. Daebakkkkkkkk!
Two stalls selling good Hokkien Prawn Mee. Tell the uncles you're bringing the food to Bangkok and they'll pack it nicely for you!
The nasi lemak at Hi Leskmi (#01-24) is super comforting.
Must try kim beef noodle!!!
Nice Hokkien Prawn Noodle and Rojak
Must try Tong Fong Fatt Boneless chicken rice  at #01-35 .. Cheap and Good
BBQ crab!!!
Singapore Hokkien Mee and duck rice. Rojak is over rated. Other stores that are not too bad too - Uncle Sim, wanton mee...
Beng Kee Wanton Noodle @ Blk 91, #01-20, signature fried dumplings the best.
Fried carrot cake: Whampoa Carrot Cake #01-06 prepares d tastier of d 2 stalls selling this dish. But not as good as places like Upp Boon Keng ;-) Plus cook is a jolly fella :-D
Satay bee Hoon must try!!!! Love e peanut taste!
Fried carrot cake sticks in the morning till 1130 or so!
Rojack stall act blur or wat. Ask for $5 no chilli but give chilli. Went bk exchg end up give super small serving bk. Hello I ordered $5
So the corner fish steamboat's batang fish not that fresh... Dunno why so many people eating
Balestier Road Hoover Rojak #01-06 is really good!
morning market, fish soup beehon, awesome!
财利鱼头炉- a definite bad choice for fish head beehoon. Worst ever.
Great Lor Mee can b found here
Many good here! The pt is food are reasonable prices! 80 cents for a kopi, noodle from sgd3! This 肉挫面have a special vinegar, the meat ball have 吊片（干鱿鱼碎），thats delicious!
The satay here is crap 
How Hup BBQ Seafood is the best.. Die die must try (",)
Oyster omelette is nice!!!
Look for the wanton noodles!
Woodlands Branch Hot Plate BBQ Fish is not bad. I like the stingray and fried kang kong. Zan Ji Mixed Veg Rice is good too
balestier road Hoover Rojak $3/$4/$5 sooo yummy!!!
Lai Lai fish soup is delicious
holy! the ah pek at huat heng fried oyster takes his time, but that means he fries till he is happy. and if he is happy, u eat also happy! juicy oysters, yummy egg and flour wow!
Their warm sweet tofu is very smooth and silky.
Zan ji mixed veg rice is slightly pricier than Uncle Sim Home cooked Nyonya food
Hainanese curry rice: Fancy eating this 4 bfast? Curry Rice #01-13 operates 7am-11am only. Plenty of fans flock to & eat around d stall. Q typically long but moves fast. Typical menu, curry is light
Balestier Road Hoover Rojak is good. The duck rice store beside it is nice as well 👍👍
Lor mee. For $3 only there's lots of ingredients, gravy doesn't turn watery and you can add all the vinegar, chilli and minced garlic you want.
Chicken Fried Rice..Awesome
Also excellent hand made dumplings and spicy laksa.
Long queue at the duck rice stall #01-07. Yummy!
A new  stall 91 prawn noodle   , so so only
Traffic warden always here!
Fried prawn noodle in the middle of the market is fantastic
Duck rice at 01-07 not too bad,  but quite overrated. Soup is so-so. The one at Geylang Bahru is better.
One my favourite local hawker but since aft the revamp, much the nice hawker had stopped. Especially in the past the nasi lemak uncle who sell in the night with no license, the chicken is the best.
Carrot Cake's great. Home made and uses 100% vegetable oil.
best one is the nan xiang chicken rice @#01-21 really very yummy been patronising it for years
Favourite food here is Hokkien Mee !
Lai Lai handmade noodles - I love the fish soup
#01-13 Curry Rice morning side! Must try! 9/10.
hoover rojak for sure, old man is fantastic skill. Young man ,can b good after sometime.
Seafood and durian are great hahaa
Loy kee chicken rice and steamboat! Not oily and healthy meal!
Prawn noodle is unknowingly long & surprisingly awful ~
I had very nice fried chicken wings at $1 each. yum.
Nice carrot with good service! And the porridge is good too! 4/5!!
Whampoa Carrot Cake is the best in town!
Bee Guan Coffee Stall @ 01-23. Brew good coffee and tea. Not to forget the boss is a cheerful man with outlook in life :)
Must try the chicken shreds noodles by housing ming ji wanton noodles!
Ah Hock Fried Oyster Hougang since 1927. #01-54 yummy.
Hoover rojak best century egg and fish egg ota shiok
One of the best ban mian in Singapore! Try the Bao bei ban mian
My fav curry rice stall. Queue started as early as 7am and the stall close at 11am. You will be amazed with ppl eating 2 bowls of rice for breakfast!
Chinese stall serving nice Mee Siam here
Whampoa stingray is nice. Should give a try!
Economical bee hoon: Lotsa stalls hawking dis bfast staple but 3 stalls stand out: 01-20, 01-21 & 01-48. Q up!
Hoover rojak and duck rice! Shiok. And yummy.
Duck rice and rabiah malaysian food is tasty!
猪肉冻 from 幸福潮州小食 #01-04 Nice!
Fried Fish Soup thumbs up !
Usual long queue @ mid section Malay dishes stall ,  tasty cooked food freshly prepared yummy curry vegetables - only misses are the lady overcharged me $1 twice for same set of dishes ordered
$18 grilled crab at #01-83! Love how the crab is not dry despite being grilled!
The hokkien mee is a MUSTTRY!!
Lifang congee serving restaurant quality food
Love the chicken rice thai tofu !!!
#01~58's ice kachang is the best!!!! Asked for more of their yummy red beans, got a mountain and all for just $1.40
Whampoa Hoover Rojak is spicy & the best !!
#01-72 bak ku mee NICE!!! Must try
Must try the duck rice and the rojak. Both next to each other. Balestier Rd Hoover Rojak yummy.
Kuay chap 4/5, hokkien mee. 3/5 cos I find that they chop the noodles too finely. Satay bee hoon 4/5 !
Duck wing the best!
Fried hokkien me here queue super long, but taste so so nia
Go http://aspirant1981.wordpress.com/2012/01/26/food-kids-meal-at-whampoa-wet-market-singapore/ to read what's good & what's not here.
Curry/sardine puffs: I get my fix fr stall 01-18 Nurilah. Go early. Their snacks sell out fast. They also hv limited kueh lopeh on weekends
Oyster omelette (orh neng) is good!
Very good morning market to get your local breakfast.
Fried Kway Teow at #01-59. Loved it. And very good service.
Great local foods @_@
Mee siam is damn nice!
The duck rice is overrated, if you didn't buy Hoover Rojak you haven't been here!

Handmade noodles: China Whampoa #01-24 serves a variety of handmade noodles in d morning, incl 'ban mian'. Generous ingredients: prawns, pork balls, fish slices. So yummy that we'd drink up d soup :-P
Buy mee pok for lunch
Slurp up every drop of fish head steamboat, a rich stock of grouper or pomfret bobbing with thick slices of fish, prawn, squid, cabbage, & sour plum. More places to eat like a local: tandl.me/12ufz7c
Had BBQ chicken wings, satay, hokkien noodles tonight..burp... All good!!
Chicken rice and mee siam not bad
Not worth the queue.rice is soggy,meat is normal,skin is fatty.
Try the Malay Chicken rice at blk 91 market.It has ginger and the chicken is super crispy.You should try.Its 1 of the best chciken rice in Central area.Sorry i forget the shop name.I give 5 🌟.
Black carrot cake is awesome make sure ypu order with spicy.
Malay stall at block 90.nice food
Looking for nice and crispy you tiao, butterfly and Goreng Pisang? Yes, you can find it at Delisnacks - Whampoa Hawker Blk 91 #01-01. They have lot of nice stuffs! Check it out!
Try 01-27 fish soup 5 bucks, with plenty of smooth fish.
Never never eat the so called famous Nasi Lemak store here. Saw the owner mixed a plate of rice that was dropped onto floor back into the pot!
This bowl was for S$5/= add but chilli padi and soup tasted superbly wonderful but given very little or just enough for my appetite
Duck rice: #01-06 sees long q's daily but 4 my family, it wasn't worth d wait. Porridge was clumpy. Thot it was yam rice but cdnt find any bits. Duck was tasty but d 'lor' (sauce) was starchy :-(
Try the Chinese tau gua and thumbs up for chinese tau gua and satay at stall #01-13 - Satay Guan
You tiao, with coffee makes my day~!!
Love the hokkien mee here! Just dropped by to buy it.
Coffee powder and chinese tea leaves for sale at 01-897
Lor mee: D stall #01-19 claims 2 b d "Best Lu Mian in Town" & it doesnt disappoint. Thick & tasty sauce in piping hot bowl. Yum!
Kway Chap: Craving dis comfort food? Head straight 2 01-26 & join d queue
Went out to buy saging na saba but went home with this.
Duck rice....
Whampoa barbeque chicken wings is a MUst try here!
Xiao long bao and Guo tie
block 91, #01-29 great homemade fish noodles, but come before 11a if you don't wanna wait 30 mins
Fish ball noodles here are great. 01-1415. Breakfast and lunch only. Same stall sells fish head steamboat in the evening
Beng kee wanton Mee is superb!
Beef noodles. Hokkien mee. Fish beehoon. My must-eats.
Singapore Hokkien Mee is good! Cockles also not bad!
Singapore fried hokkien mee and lai Lai fish soup is mad awesome!!!
Try Chi Ni Dou Fu for dessert stall #01-71
LOUSY. Cuisine Teochew porridge #01-53
Famous lost & found wantan sucks!
Highly recommend Block 91 (morning market) Traditional Handmade Yong Tau Foo inner a little (along same stretch as the Prawn Noodles). Kopi/Teh is cheaper beside this. Nearby a banjiankuay shop
singapore fried prawn noodles is overrated. i've had better ones sold by hawkers with better manners. thankfully, balestier road hoover rojak made the trip worthwhile.
block 91, #01-29 great homemade noodles with seafood broth, but come before 11a if you don't wanna wait 30 mins
#01-10 Best seafood stall ever. Sedapp!
Braised Duck porridge next to Hoover Rojak...SHIOK!
Robert MeeSiam. Plain & simple version. I rate 6.5/10
Yes, the Hoover rojak got standard
Teochew kueh: Tanglin Halt A1 #01-34 sells fried carrot cake (w lotsa garlic). However, look closer & u will find "soon kueh" & "png kueh". Ask 4 them 2 b fried lightly if u want them warmed up :-)
Best chicken rice i try so far, great chili chicken very smooth. Try out one day,
Try the China Whampoa Home Made Noodle at #01-24. Tasty but be prepared to wait 25-30mins on a busy day!!

Do not order the cuttlefish kangkong(jiu hur eng cai) from Liang Liang Cooked Food(#01-16 whampoa blk 90 market)Pathetic..i really mean pathetic portion(can literally count the number of strands of ka
Wantan mee: D better (not best) of d 3 stalls in d mkt r "1.90" #01-36 & Pontian #01-40 (predictable taste)
Fried hokkien mee: Skip the famous #01-32 and try #01-59. Thank me later.
Frog porridge at #01-85 is worth a try!
The 天福活田鸡 (01-84) simply sucks. The meat is very "old". DO NOT EAT!
You got to try the teowchew noodles - superb!
1.90 wanton noodles is over rated. I tried it on Sunday Morning 11:15am. Char siew cannot make it, wanton cannot .make it, noodles also over cooked. Just take the rojak and go. Worth the money.
#1-39 (545 Whampoa Prawn Noodle) $5 portion. Overall ok, soup lacks punch
Teochew noodles: Simple, elegant bfast @ Teochew Kway Teow Mee #01-07. Reminded me of noodle portions in the old days, when everything wasn't supersized up. Clean taste, basic ingredients
Breakfast serving fr Kampong Wanton Noodles #01-42 was passable. Egg noodle had interesting bite fr usual noodle stalls. Shocked that some char siew slices were cold (overnight?)
Go for the hokkien mee! Savoury~ The duck rice is good too. And the rojak is island-famous!
#01-32 Traditional Handmade Yong Taut Futhe noodles is soggy...
Love the grandma's pancake!
Try the fruit juice stall at 01-62
Curry rice #01-13. Only opened from 7am to 11am.
The hokkien mee n Xiao long Bao are really really awesome!
A myriad of food choices here with Hoover's Rojak being one of the most popular. Liang Liang Satay Beehoon was okay, same goes for the Hoover's Fish Soup.
Kopi: 2 of the better kopi stalls r 0103 Coffee Stall #01-03, & Bee Guan #01-23. Brews r stronger & more fragrant. & none of that tepid sour aftertaste
Wow the popiah at the vegetarian stall very salty...beside the chicken rice stall. Eat until I feel like vomit😨
Try the 新华 fried noodles, very good..
Friend store mum mum,   Seafood
There's home-made barley at #01-09!
Whampoa Carrot Cake is quite nice. Worth 3.5/5. #01-06
Fried oyster at 01-54 also mediocre. Don't be fooled by its "since 1927".....
Fish porridge: Hoover Fish Porridge #01-56 is d plc 4 ur fix of fresh fish slices served in a soupy bowl of bee hoon, mee sua or porridge. Q moves quite fast. If u pref fried ver, go 2 Lai Lai #01-16
#01-17 soya bean curd is like uber smmmmooooothhhhh! Ps: this store is in the part of the market parallel to the wet market
The food here so so nia....this will be the last time.....
Deep fried carrot cake is a must have(:
BBQ chicken wings: We usu order fr stall #01-83. Prompt & friendly. & if u njoy fresh cockles, they serve dat too ;-)
Wide range of food 
Balestier Road Hoover Rojak
Duck rice, Rabiah muslim food, Laksmi nasi lemak, char kway teow, and Singapore hokkien noodle is my favourite stall of all time.
Foodie paradise. Cheap. Tasty. Variety.
The popiah is quite sucky.
Chicken rice: Nan Xiang #01-21 @ Blk 90 is a good alternative if u don't want to queue or walk over to Blk 91 for Loy Kee. Generous portions, skin was springy
Back choir mee
Thumbs up for Lai Lai Fried Fish Soup !
Stingray fish and fried dumplings all good!
Try the  Ba ku teh.It taste good!
The malay food is superb!! Tho is slightly pricey 
Rojak: There r 2 stalls: d famous Hoover Rojak (#01-06) & Mun Theng Fang #01-87. We always order fr d latter cos' we can taste d freshly-shaved bamboo shoots. Plus it's run by an old couple ;-)
Like Fried Fish Soup here
Prawn noodles to die for although the waiting time is around 30 mins during weekends.
Prawn mee at 01-25 soso. Nothing special.
Hokkien (prawn) noodles: Instead of long q @ #01-32, we order fr Qin Li #01-50. Plenty of gusto goes in2 frying. Like part when chef covers wok to trap steam 2 infuse d prawn stock in. Slurp!
the fish head steamboat is best...
Zhong He beer stall has great service from a dashing little beer girl.
Chicken rice's thai tofu is awesome! Cripsy and soft on the inside!
The pig's liver in the satay beehoon from Liang Liang Cooked Food is fresh and nicely done. Yums!
Pork bones!!!!
Try the prawn noodles! It's delicious! Do come before 7am to avoid the long queue
The Singapore fried hokkien mew sstall is super nice! ^^ ♥♥
Hungry? Go http://aspirant1981.wordpress.com/2012/01/26/food-kids-meal-at-whampoa-wet-market-singapore/ to check out the nearby Whampoa Market Food Centre
Craving for chwee kueh during bfast? There's Tiong Bahru Chwee Kueh #01-25. But compared 2 actual Tiong Bahru stall, there's no fragrance fr d 'chai por' (chopped radish) toppings. V bland :-(
Fish head steamboat is all-time fav! Thhe beancurd sold in the morn is really good too!
Avoid 'old Chong pang'. Not honest, order a piece of squid, came only few thin slices, food over cooked. Never am I gonna buy from them
The Malay rice here has a good variety but come early to avoid the long queue and food being sold out! the fried chicken drum stick is delicious! A must try! 
Lor Mie here is not bad though the aunty is a bit 'hao lien' --"
Prawn noodles: 545 Whampoa Prawn Noodles #01-39 is d locals' fave bfast spot. Soup base is savoury thick. However, expect to wait (we waited 20mins!)
Sam's orchard fresh fruit and juice! Good service with fresh cooling fruits
Must try;  *Tong Fong Fatt Boneless Chicken Rice, * Eastern Chicken Rice (Before 12 noon), *Mung Teng Fang Rojak, *Satay Guan, *Siang Guan Sugar Cane Juice..
Don't 01-36 wanton noodle, signboard said $1.90 but sell @ $2.50
Black carrot cake bestest
A handful of tasty food around. The standard of the foods are quite consistent. You have to hunt for it.
Affordable festive plants. During CNY period, open area next to carpark turns into florists' wholesale showcase. We saved 30% compared to Far East Flora for the same plants. More $ left for gambling!
